String matching algorithm targeting DNA sequencing.

Please, contact davide.pietrobon@berkeley.edu for bugs, comments, and suggestions.

Have a good one!

Two files are present at the moment:
1- a python script with testing routines
2- a more systematic piece of software in cpp
   compile with:
   g++ -O kdiff_lib.hpp kdiff_strmatch.cpp -o kdiff_strmatch.x

   Run with -h option to print the help.

   Example:
   ./kdiff_strmatch.x -e 'TAGTC' -i 'example/sequence.fasta' -o 'example/sequence_trimmed.fasta' -v -k 1

